WEBVTT

00:02.930 --> 00:04.329
I never stopped loving you.

00:07.040 --> 00:09.759
Aria, they're gonna market
the hell out of this book.

00:09.770 --> 00:12.500
- It's gonna be huge.
- Oh, my God, we did it.

00:13.310 --> 00:15.505
I lied to you earlier, Aria.
I did see Ali.

00:15.510 --> 00:17.330
And I'm pretty sure she
confessed to killing Charlotte.

00:17.350 --> 00:18.772
We don't have time
to debate this.

00:18.780 --> 00:21.146
Right now, Alison is safely
locked up at Welby

00:21.150 --> 00:23.948
and Hanna is life
/5 on the llhe.

00:23.950 --> 00:27.386
(Elliott)
I ’m gonna make sure
you live a long life

00:27.390 --> 00:28.709
rotting away in here.

00:28.720 --> 00:30.608
I know you killed Charlotte.

00:30.630 --> 00:33.019
Stop! Please, you have
to help me, please.

00:43.140 --> 00:44.835
Are you sure about this?

00:44.840 --> 00:46.637
Yes, I'm sure.

00:46.640 --> 00:48.505
If someone tried to hurt you,
the police—-

00:48.510 --> 00:51.149
I have to talk to my friends
before I do anything.

00:51.150 --> 00:52.208
I understand.

00:55.150 --> 00:57.880
You're a friend
of my niece, of Alison.

00:59.560 --> 01:01.516
I never said anything
about Alison.

01:01.520 --> 01:04.159
I can tell by the way
that you're looking at me.

01:04.160 --> 01:06.685
You knew my sister Jessica,
Alison's mother

01:06.700 --> 01:08.827
so you must be a friend
of Alison's.

01:08.830 --> 01:10.092
Ali never mentioned anything

01:10.100 --> 01:12.591
about her mother
havrng a srster.

01:12.600 --> 01:14.898
Let alone a twin sister.??

01:14.900 --> 01:18.438
- What's your name?
- Hanna.

01:18.440 --> 01:21.102
Families are very complicated
things, Hanna.

01:21.110 --> 01:23.237
Yeah, I've noticed.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.343
Many families have secrets.

01:25.350 --> 01:28.012
Most families, really.

01:28.020 --> 01:31.342
And sometimes, those secrets
are actual people.

01:33.190 --> 01:35.852
Imagine that.

01:35.860 --> 01:38.124
And that's who you are?

01:38.130 --> 01:39.586
One of those secret people?

01:41.230 --> 01:42.857
Not anymore.

01:47.070 --> 01:49.459
Got a secret
can you keep It?

01:49.470 --> 01:52.234
Swear this one you'll save

01:52.240 --> 01:57.234
Better lock it in your pocket
taking this one to the grave

01:57.250 --> 02:02.119
If I show you then I know
you won't tell what I said

02:02.120 --> 02:07.240
'Cause two can keep a secret
if one of them is dead

02:09.430 --> 02:10.488
(Ezra)
'Here, Hanna.‘

02:15.460 --> 02:17.599
Hanna, are you sure you don't
want to go to the doctor?

02:17.600 --> 02:19.921
- I'm sure.
- Hanna, I think you should.

02:19.940 --> 02:22.431
The doctors _
are gonna ask questions.

02:22.440 --> 02:25.159
And then, I'll have to lie.
No doctors, no questions.

02:26.440 --> 02:29.932
Hanna, I'm sorry,
but you have to tell us

02:29.950 --> 02:32.601
about Mary Drake
picking you up.

02:32.620 --> 02:34.042
Is she real?

02:34.050 --> 02:36.974
I mean, is she really
who she says she is?

02:36.990 --> 02:38.446
We think so.

02:38.450 --> 02:40.645
(Spencer)
'Yeah, she was a patient
at Radley.‘

02:40.660 --> 02:43.049
- We found her file.
- What?

02:43.060 --> 02:46.154
She's Alison's aunt,
Charlotte's biological mother.

02:46.160 --> 02:48.094
The DiLaurentis family
adopted Charlotte.

02:50.330 --> 02:52.867
So it's her.

02:52.870 --> 02:56.294
Mary Drake, she's been
after us all along.

02:56.310 --> 02:58.164
Someone killed her daughter

02:58.170 --> 03:01.571
and then she shows up
to get even.

03:01.580 --> 03:02.877
Yeah, we're pretty sure
she didn't show up

03:02.880 --> 03:04.677
just to get into
the resort business.

03:04.680 --> 03:07.308
She must have been chasing me
when I got out.

03:07.320 --> 03:09.015
But why wouldn't
she just run me over

03:09.020 --> 03:10.647
instead of bringing me here?

03:10.650 --> 03:13.585
Because we gave her
exactly what she wanted.

03:16.160 --> 03:18.253
Charlotte's killer?

03:18.260 --> 03:20.649
We're convinced it's Alison.

03:20.660 --> 03:21.991
We found evidence.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.252
[sighs]

03:24.270 --> 03:27.569
Spencer, can I have something
stronger than coffee in here?

03:27.570 --> 03:28.798
Yeah.

03:38.180 --> 03:39.602
This belongs to you.

03:47.860 --> 03:48.918
Thanks.

03:48.920 --> 03:50.387
[knock on door]

03:50.390 --> 03:51.721
Oh, that's Mona.

03:51.730 --> 03:53.425
Well, be careful
in case it isn't.

03:53.430 --> 03:55.250
[cell phone vibrates]

03:59.870 --> 04:02.839
Well, there was nobody there,
just this.

04:08.440 --> 04:10.203
"Couldn't have done it
wrthout you.

04:10.210 --> 04:12.508
Glad we're on the same team.
A.D."

04:20.890 --> 04:22.517
[door creaking]

04:24.560 --> 04:25.788
It's from Lucas.

04:31.930 --> 04:33.898
Sit down. I can do that.

04:33.900 --> 04:35.993
I can boil my own water.
Thanks.

04:38.240 --> 04:39.400
[Emily clears throat]

04:41.240 --> 04:43.128
Can I, uh, borrow you
for a minute?

04:53.760 --> 04:56.183
So are you gonna take
Lucas up on his offer?

04:56.190 --> 04:57.987
[sighs]
He's crazy.

04:57.990 --> 04:59.582
He sees your potential.

04:59.600 --> 05:01.022
Potential for what?

05:01.030 --> 05:02.827
For what you could do
if you were in charge.

05:02.830 --> 05:04.457
Caleb, haven't you noticed?

05:04.470 --> 05:08.839
None of us are in charge
of anything around here.

05:08.840 --> 05:10.364
Well, we can fix that.

05:10.370 --> 05:12.429
No one's giving up on anybody.

05:12.440 --> 05:13.759
Then what?

05:13.780 --> 05:16.101
Suppose we get through that..

05:16.110 --> 05:17.998
...where does that leave us?

05:18.010 --> 05:20.069
Back to where we started?

05:20.080 --> 05:22.139
Well, I guess it depends
on how far back we wanna go.

05:25.820 --> 05:28.550
[sighs]
Look, in that room
at the resort

05:28.560 --> 05:30.152
before all the lights went off

05:30.160 --> 05:33.880
and someone pushed me down
a hole, I was scared.

05:35.030 --> 05:36.850
Me too.

05:36.870 --> 05:39.668
But you were there.

05:39.670 --> 05:44.266
I always felt safe around you.

05:44.270 --> 05:46.409
Even when we weren't getting
along, you made me feel safe.

05:50.380 --> 05:53.577
Maybe that's why
what happened happened..

05:53.580 --> 05:55.946
...with us.

05:55.950 --> 05:57.770
So you think we just went back

05:57.790 --> 06:00.008
to what we _used to be
for a minute?

06:00.020 --> 06:01.089
Yeah.

06:03.060 --> 06:04.482
Only for a minute.

06:08.200 --> 06:09.656
Where is Spencer?

06:16.870 --> 06:19.703
- Hey, you okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

06:19.710 --> 06:22.634
Uh, I just wanted to be
by myself for a minute.

06:25.380 --> 06:27.245
I think we're all feeling
a little lost right now.

06:27.250 --> 06:28.672
I'm fine.

06:31.650 --> 06:33.811
Do you think Ali's safe?

06:33.820 --> 06:35.412
At Welby?

06:35.420 --> 06:37.615
I mean, places like that
are designed to keep people

06:37.630 --> 06:40.224
from getting out,
not from getting in.

06:40.230 --> 06:42.152
Maybe we need to warn Elliott.

06:42.160 --> 06:43.650
Well, what do you
wanna tell him?

06:43.670 --> 06:45.558
'That we told someone his wife'

06:45.570 --> 06:48.266
killed her own sister_
who's actually her cousm?

06:48.270 --> 06:50.067
I mean, he'd lock us up.

06:50.070 --> 06:51.628
Spencer.

06:51.640 --> 06:54.302
Hey, how about I take you home?

06:54.310 --> 06:56.574
- Yeah.
- Okay.

07:00.350 --> 07:03.069
Em, keep an eye on Hanna.

07:05.350 --> 07:08.683
- You feel it too?
- Yeah, she's got that look.

07:08.690 --> 07:10.157
The dollhouse look.

07:13.800 --> 07:15.153
Bye.

07:18.930 --> 07:20.067
Do you wanna give Jordan a call?

07:23.470 --> 07:25.267
And tell him what?

07:25.270 --> 07:27.864
That I got myself
a little kidnapped for a while?

07:27.880 --> 07:29.438
Maybe you just wanna hear
his voice.

07:30.950 --> 07:33.544
It's too late to call him now.
I'll do it later.

07:36.120 --> 07:37.109
[sighs]

07:44.160 --> 07:46.025
Hey, aren't you tired?

07:47.630 --> 07:52.226
Um, no, I shot past tired
a long time ago.

07:52.230 --> 07:54.494
Well, we should probably
get some sleep while we can.

07:54.500 --> 07:56.639
Yeah, I just have to finish
this up for my mom.

07:58.140 --> 07:59.801
Turns out
there's way more paperwork

07:59.810 --> 08:01.539
when you win instead of lose.

08:03.710 --> 08:07.874
Our love is six feet under

08:07.880 --> 08:12.385
I can't help
but wonder if our..

08:12.390 --> 08:14.415
I'm really glad
that Hanna's safe.

08:16.020 --> 08:17.351
We all are.

08:17.360 --> 08:19.885
That was so dangerous.
I should've stopped her.

08:21.230 --> 08:25.166
You know, Hanna's like
an aircraft carrier.

08:25.170 --> 08:27.821
Lot of firepower, but
pretty difficult to maneuver.

08:31.410 --> 08:34.664
Yeah, well, I guess they call
ships "she" for a reason, huh?

08:36.680 --> 08:40.172
You trace my lips

08:40.180 --> 08:42.569
Erase your touch..

08:42.580 --> 08:45.686
- Come to bed.
- I will soon.

08:45.690 --> 08:48.955
Too much for me

08:52.060 --> 08:56.326
Ooh

08:58.930 --> 09:03.958
Ooh

09:05.840 --> 09:08.229
Again

09:08.240 --> 09:10.629
[cell phone ringing]

09:22.820 --> 09:23.855
Hello.

09:23.860 --> 09:26.078
[woman gasping over phone]

09:26.090 --> 09:28.320
Hello?

09:28.330 --> 09:31.197
(Alison)
'Help me.‘

09:31.200 --> 09:33.498
Who is this?

09:33.500 --> 09:35.832
(Alison)
'Help me, Emily.'

09:35.840 --> 09:37.694
Ali?

09:37.710 --> 09:39.200
'Em, I need you.‘

09:40.440 --> 09:41.429
[Alison sobs]

09:41.440 --> 09:43.829
Ali, are you alright?

09:45.010 --> 09:46.671
- 'Let go.‘
- Hello.

09:46.680 --> 09:49.114
- 'Give me the phone.‘
- 'No. No.‘

09:49.120 --> 09:51.680
[Alison grunting]

09:52.820 --> 09:54.515
Ali?

09:54.520 --> 09:56.556
[phone disconnects]

10:01.700 --> 10:03.827
No, you made a mistake.
I visited her the other day.

10:03.830 --> 10:05.491
I'm the one
that brought her here.

10:05.500 --> 10:08.537
Mrs. Rollins' visiting
instructions have been changed.

10:08.540 --> 10:11.293
- Family only.
- W-why did they change?

10:11.310 --> 10:12.538
Did something happen?

10:12.540 --> 10:14.861
All I can tell you
is the only visitors

10:14.880 --> 10:17.508
she'_s allowed
are family members.

10:17.510 --> 10:20.479
Is Dr. Rollins here?
Can you page him, please?

10:20.480 --> 10:21.913
Dr. Rollins
is right over there.

10:26.190 --> 10:28.886
- Elliott.
- Emily.

10:28.890 --> 10:30.585
Thank you.

10:30.590 --> 10:32.820
They won't let me in
to see Ali.

10:32.830 --> 10:34.889
Those are my instructions.

10:34.900 --> 10:37.050
Is she alright?
Has something happened?

10:40.870 --> 10:42.997
I've decided
Alison will be better off

10:43.010 --> 10:44.830
in isolation right now.

10:44.840 --> 10:46.705
Okay, can I just
see her for a minute?

10:46.710 --> 10:49.679
It's not in Ali's
best interests

10:49.680 --> 10:51.432
or yours.

10:51.450 --> 10:54.669
So, when can she have visitors?

10:54.680 --> 10:56.910
As soon as I think she can,
I'll call you.

10:56.920 --> 10:58.842
[cell phone rings]

10:58.850 --> 11:00.989
I have to go. I'm sorry.

11:02.920 --> 11:04.319
Thanks.

11:05.860 --> 11:08.852
[dramatic music]

11:17.110 --> 11:20.864
(Lucas)
So how is Alison doing?

11:20.880 --> 11:22.939
I heard she was
in the hospital.

11:22.940 --> 11:24.737
I wish people would
just leave her alone.

11:24.750 --> 11:27.207
I was just asking
how she's doing.

11:27.220 --> 11:30.075
Sorry.

11:30.090 --> 11:34.413
- So how are you?
- I'm kinda tired.

11:34.420 --> 11:36.149
Did you get the package
that I sent over?

11:38.590 --> 11:41.286
Lucas, why are you
doing this for me?

11:41.300 --> 11:42.927
I mean, you could be out

11:42.930 --> 11:45.069
building some
private spaceship or something.

11:45.070 --> 11:46.321
The private spaceship market

11:46.330 --> 11:48.798
is a little overcrowded
at the moment.

11:48.800 --> 11:51.598
- Did you look at the papers?
- There were a lot of them.

11:51.610 --> 11:54.602
Lot of those little
"Sign here" stickers.

11:54.610 --> 11:56.237
Why do you make it
so hard for somebody

11:56.240 --> 11:58.401
to do something nice for you?

11:58.410 --> 12:00.298
Why do you resist it so much?

12:00.320 --> 12:04.609
Look, Lucas, I think you think
I'm somebody I'm not.

12:04.620 --> 12:06.508
Everyone thinks
I'm somebody I'm not.

12:06.520 --> 12:08.909
Somebody smarter..

12:08.920 --> 12:10.319
...braver, sharper.

12:12.860 --> 12:14.282
But I'm not.

12:14.300 --> 12:17.849
Yes, you are.
That's the point.

12:17.870 --> 12:19.792
Hanna, I think you want this.

12:19.800 --> 12:21.495
Otherwise,
I wouldn't have offered it.

12:22.670 --> 12:24.638
But I do need an answer.

12:24.640 --> 12:25.959
We need to file a business plan

12:25.970 --> 12:28.473
or we're gonna lose
the tax credit.

12:28.480 --> 12:30.300
Look, I'm just saying,
I'm not the best person

12:30.310 --> 12:32.540
when it comes
to making deCISIons.

12:32.550 --> 12:34.575
Well, Hanna,
not making a decision..

12:35.880 --> 12:37.142
...that's a decision.

12:39.760 --> 12:41.409
If you could've heard her
on the phone.

12:41.420 --> 12:43.684
Maybe she killed Charlotte,
maybe she didn't.

12:43.690 --> 12:45.920
We can't just leave her in there
with no one protecting her.

12:45.930 --> 12:47.989
Okay, well, did you tell
Elliott about the call?

12:48.000 --> 12:50.321
No, I didn't want him to know
who she was calling.

12:50.330 --> 12:51.649
So, where did you leave
things with him?

12:51.670 --> 12:53.092
He said he'll call me
when she Improves.

12:53.100 --> 12:54.419
But I don't think we can wait.

12:54.440 --> 12:57.000
[cell phone rings]

12:58.340 --> 13:01.503
Um, it's my work.
I'll call them back.

13:01.510 --> 13:03.831
- What about Mary Drake?
- What about her?

13:03.850 --> 13:06.671
She's family, she has access,
you know?

13:06.680 --> 13:07.999
Should we try and use her?

13:08.020 --> 13:10.511
Ask Mary to take us
to see Ali?

13:10.520 --> 13:12.545
Em, we think this woman
might be Uber A.

13:12.550 --> 13:14.108
- You wanna ask her to help?
- Okay.

13:14.120 --> 13:15.758
Maybe it's better
that we go in there with her

13:15.760 --> 13:18.183
than let her go in
by herself.

13:18.190 --> 13:20.351
No, we can't take that chance.

13:23.100 --> 13:26.228
I think we both saw this coming.

13:26.230 --> 13:28.369
Apparently, one of us saw it
before the other.

13:28.370 --> 13:29.962
I'm sorry.

13:29.970 --> 13:31.130
[sighs]

13:31.140 --> 13:32.767
Yeah, so am I.

13:32.770 --> 13:34.431
It's just coming home

13:34.440 --> 13:36.271
and seeing my friends
and everything

13:36.280 --> 13:38.703
that Ali's going through
I realize I've got a lot

13:38.710 --> 13:40.541
of unresolved things in my life

13:40.550 --> 13:42.313
and it wouldn't be fair to you.

13:42.320 --> 13:44.276
I think you want me
to say "Thank you"

13:44.290 --> 13:46.110
but I'm not going to.

13:46.120 --> 13:47.815
No, I just want you
to understand.

13:47.820 --> 13:49.811
I've gotta work through
these things.

13:49.830 --> 13:53.652
It doesn't have anything to do
with the book or Ezra.

13:53.660 --> 13:55.059
[sighs]
It's all me.

13:55.060 --> 13:57.221
It's just about you and me.

13:57.230 --> 14:01.326
Yeah. I'm sorry--

14:01.340 --> 14:03.228
Aria, I think you don't
have to say that anymore.

14:03.240 --> 14:04.662
(Aria)
'I'm. .'

14:04.670 --> 14:06.103
[sighs]

14:06.110 --> 14:08.135
[sighs]

14:12.750 --> 14:15.913
I got a surprise too.

14:15.920 --> 14:17.478
It's not as big
as yours, but, um..

14:19.520 --> 14:21.078
I'm back on the book.

14:21.090 --> 14:22.352
'That's what I came here
to tell you.‘

14:22.360 --> 14:23.952
- You're back on the book?
- Yeah.

14:23.960 --> 14:25.655
I convinced Jillian
that I'd be able to prep

14:25.660 --> 14:28.652
the manuscript faster than
anyone else, and she agreed.

14:28.660 --> 14:30.150
You're gonna edit the book?

14:30.170 --> 14:33.128
More that I'll be a kind
of creative gatekeeper.

14:33.130 --> 14:34.825
Make sure everything goes well

14:34.840 --> 14:38.162
and everybody stays
reasonably happy.

14:39.640 --> 14:41.938
Do we have a problem?

14:41.940 --> 14:44.329
I-I don't know. Do we?

14:51.050 --> 14:53.518
You worked hard for this.

14:53.520 --> 14:56.182
I'd like to see you get
something you've always wanted.

14:59.060 --> 15:01.028
We're almost there, aren't we?

15:02.900 --> 15:04.299
Yeah, almost.

15:05.670 --> 15:08.366
Then we'll do it.

15:08.370 --> 15:09.962
We'll make it work.

15:09.970 --> 15:11.961
Yeah, at least we can cross
the finish line together.

15:16.540 --> 15:17.609
[Liam sighs]

15:21.650 --> 15:23.049
[sighs]

15:30.760 --> 15:32.648
Not just first class.

15:32.660 --> 15:35.925
First class, front row,
window, the side with the door.

15:38.170 --> 15:40.320
Because she has to be
the last one on the plane

15:40.340 --> 15:41.762
and the ﬁrst one off.

15:43.840 --> 15:45.865
No, don't say you'll try,
just do it.

15:45.870 --> 15:49.237
Girls and boys they enjoy

15:49.240 --> 15:53.279
In a love that destroys

15:53.280 --> 15:56.647
Stack them in let them win..

